<DOC><DOCNO> AP890510-0167 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-10-89 2011EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Shamir     05-10 0222</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Shamir,0228</SECOND><HEAD>Shamir Hospitalized for Tests, Reported in Good Condition</HEAD><DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Prime Minister Yitzhak Shamir has beenhospitalized for tests after complaining of tiredness and weakness,but hopes to be released by Friday, his spokesman said.   Shamir, 73, was taken to Hadassah Hospital in Jerusalem after hebecame faint Wednesday while attending Israel's annual IndependenceDay Bible contest, spokesman Avi Pazner said.   The prime minister had attended more than half a dozen eventssince Monday night to mark two successive holidays, Memorial Dayand Independence Day.   Pazner said Shamir fell against a piece of furniture in his homeTuesday, bruising his cheek, but the injury was not serious and hadno connection with his hospitalization.   Hospital spokeswoman Ruth Mekel said he was admitted ``forgeneral tests'' by Dr. Yehezkiel Stein, the hospital's director ofinternal medicine. She said he was ``resting and is feeling fine.''   His spokesman said Shamir ``hopes that in a day or two he willbe let out.'' Pazner said his boss was ``in an excellent mood ...working on his schedule from his hospital room'' and had asked thata radio and telephone be installed.   Shamir's wife Shulamit visited him and more visitors wereexpected, Pazner reported. He said the prime minister's generalhealth was ``excellent'' and he has no history of major medicalproblems.</TEXT></DOC>